<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-19T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-19T12:00:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3445: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-19T13:00:00-04:00">December 19, 1933—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>114. For the Secretary. My December 19, 11 a.m. President of League
                            Commission has informed President Ayala that the Bolivian Government
                            accepts the armistice proposed by Ayala. The Commission leaves La Paz
                            today for Montevideo where it hopes to arrive the 24th. From that time
                            it will be in Montevideo at the disposal of the plenipotentiaries of
                            Paraguay and Bolivia.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Montevideo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>